  "title": "fix(middleware): subscribe middleware after `init`",
  "body": "Subscribing the middleware before `mainIndex.init` is fine for now but it won't be as soon as we expose this API officially and that the middleware relies on a index instance variables and events because they're not yet set.\r\n\r\nI stubble across this issue while developing the InstantSearch DevTools, so users could have unintended behaviors if they also build similar middleware.\r\n\r\nNote that in the [original implementation of the router](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4224/files#diff-1fc36c4ea042d2ecb5a498416e5e0357L421-L429), it was also subscribed after `init`.",
